President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 1st to May 7th, 2016 as National Small Business Week. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of small businesses in the US economy, stating that they create nearly two-thirds of net new jobs and employ more than half of all Americans. The President pledges to support small businesses and provide them with the tools and resources they need to succeed. He mentions various initiatives, such as tax cuts and the Affordable Care Act, that have been implemented to help small businesses. Additionally, he emphasizes the need for small businesses to expand into new markets and encourages breaking down trade barriers. The President also mentions the efforts of his administration to support small businesses through federal contracts and the availability of online tools for entrepreneurs. He concludes by calling upon all Americans to recognize the contributions of small businesses to the American economy.